######################################################################################

1. How to compute difference between two n-bit numbers?

a - b = a + (-b)
observe that (-b) is the 2's complement of b, -b = ~b + 1, ~b = 1's complement of b
so a - b = RCA(a, ~b, 1)

In the circuit we can put a switch which will be connected to the carry in of the adder
and also with XOR gates with each of the input bits of b. When the switch is turned on
it will make the carry in 1 and simultaneously flip all the bits of b (XOR with 1 flips 
the bit avlue). This way we will get a-b in output. When switch is off it will not change
anything and we will get a+b in output.

######################################################################################

2. The longest delays in the circuits.

8 bit RCA
    worst delay carry out - 10.770
    worst delay sum - 10.528

16 bit RCA
    worst delay carry out - 17.541
    worst delay sum - 16.780

32 bit RCA
    worst delay carry out - 29.168
    worst delay sum - 28.833

64 bit RCA
    worst delay carry out - 55.978
    worst delay sum - 56.646

